{"article_id":"KSyZUwZNyARALOxz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The GOP ' s months-long debate","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"over when and how to send a repeal of Obamacare to the president ' s desk","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"now appears to have an answer .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"Repealing the law \" root and branch \" is probably out of the question ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"the chamber ' s parliamentarian is hinting ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"because some parts of Obamacare don ' t affect the federal budget .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"That ' s a must","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"in order to use the obscure procedure","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"known in Senate parlance as reconciliation ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"which allows lawmakers to avoid the 60-vote filibuster hurdle","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"and pass bills on a simple majority vote .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"That ' s not the GOP ' s only problem .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Under those rules any Obamacare repeal has to reduce","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"- not increase -","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"the deficit .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"So Republicans will have to pick and choose which parts of the Affordable Care Act they most want to ditch .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"Obama will , of course , veto any bill","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"that significantly damages his signature domestic policy achievement .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"But the entire process has the makings of a difficult political exercise","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"that will reveal something about the GOP ' s priorities","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"when it comes to the reviled law ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"forcing the party to go beyond the pile-on repeal rhetoric","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"and say specifically what it would do","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"and how it would pay for it .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Republicans could try to get rid of the mandates and taxes ,","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"but then they ' d have to plug a trillion-dollar hole .","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"Cut the Medicaid expansion to the states ?","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Sounds simple enough ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"but then they could put themselves at odds with governors .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"They ' ll also have to decide","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"if they want to scrap federal Obamacare subsidies , currently on the hot seat across the street at the Supreme Court ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"which this month will rule","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"whether they ' re constitutional .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Gutting them would yield almost a trillion dollars in savings ,","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"which could then be used","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"to repeal other parts of the law .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"But moderates also may experience a political backlash","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"for slashing health care tax credits for poor and middle-class families .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Extending or replacing the subsidies , though , could further limit their repeal options","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"and alienate conservatives at the same time .","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"The complex puzzle isn ' t what Republicans","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"who ' ve been vowing for years to abolish the law","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"so despised by the right","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"- the GOP-controlled House has voted dozens of times to overturn Obamacare -","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"had in mind .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"Their vow","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"to get a repeal to Obama ' s desk","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"seemed closer than ever to being realized","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"after Republicans gained control of both chambers of Congress in the midterm elections .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"But it ' s turning out to be a lot more complicated .","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"\" We went through this exercise in 2012 ,","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"and what we concluded is that","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"[ you can not repeal ] the whole thing ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"but there are a number of different things","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that you could knock out :","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"the individual mandate , ... employer mandate , the exchanges , maybe even Medicaid expansion , \"","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"said Lanhee Chen , a Hoover Institute fellow","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"who advised Mitt Romney ' s campaign -","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"which looked into what could and couldn ' t be repealed through reconciliation during the 2012 election cycle .","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"The conundrum has many on the far right urging GOP leaders to take on the Senate parliamentarian ,","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"who will ultimately rule what can and can not be repealed through reconciliation ,","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"and try to repeal the entire law","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"using a one- or two-line sentence","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"that simply reads :","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"\" Repeal the Affordable Care Act . \"","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"But policymakers and staff","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"working on the matter","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"are finding","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"it ' s not so straightforward .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"The so-called Byrd rule prevents reconciliation from being used","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"to make policy changes","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"that don ' t affect the deficit ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"which is the main goal of the fast-track procedure .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"\" We ' re really just trying to game out all of the different options","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"our members have","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"to basically repeal in whole or in part , \"","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"said one senior GOP Senate aide .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"\" We definitely are preparing to do only budgetary things . \"","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"In their budget deal , Republicans agreed to employ reconciliation narrowly","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"- namely for a repeal of Obamacare or a \" fix \" to King v. Burwell ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"should the Supreme Court in late June knock down subsidies","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"used by nearly 8 million people .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"But the parliamentarian has quietly suggested to Senate Republican aides","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"that full repeal is out of the question ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"two sources told .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"\" The message came out loud and clear","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"that total repeal won ' t work , \"","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"said Tom Miller , a health care policy expert at the right-of-center American Enterprise Institute ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"referring to private conversations on the Hill about what can and can ' t be done .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"That means Republicans will probably have to go through the ACA provision by provision","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"and strike only policies","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"that have a direct cost to Uncle Sam ,","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"what ' s known on the Hill as a \" Byrd rule scrub \" or \" Byrd bath . \"","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"Former staff ,","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"including former top GOP budget staffer Bill Hoagland ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"believe","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Republicans won ' t be able to repeal some ACA provisions","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"that affect private markets","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"but don ' t directly affect the federal budget .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Those include rules","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"that set the minimum standards of coverage","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"that insurers have to offer ;","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"requirements","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"that insurers spend a certain amount of premiums on health costs ;","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"and the prohibition","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"on denying coverage","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"because of pre-existing conditions .","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"That doesn ' t mean Republicans won ' t try .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"A senior GOP aide in the Senate told","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"they are considering arguing to the parliamentarian","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"that such provisions actually do hurt the deficit","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"and should be repealable .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"One potential case","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"they ' ll make :","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"These requirements drive up the cost of premiums ,","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"which are covered by federal subsidies ,","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"so they may increase the cost to the Treasury .","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"Some conservatives and staff in both chambers , like House Freedom Caucus Chairman Jim Jordan","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"( R-Ohio ) ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"are urging the chambers to do a straight one- or two-sentence repeal of everything .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"They argue","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"that the parliamentarian has to look only at the words in front of her during reconciliation","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"and should not be able to force lawmakers to break out the provisions on their own .","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"One aide","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"working on the matter","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"suggested","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"they may try this","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"and see","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"if it works","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"- but others are doubtful .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"There ' s also a limit","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"to what can be included in the fast-track budget process","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"because the GOP budget requires each of the five health-related committees to find $ 1 billion in savings ;","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"yet a full repeal bill in 2012 was scored as adding $ 100 billion to the deficit ,","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"according to Congress ' budget scorekeeper .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"The King case is the big X factor in all of this .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"Should SCOTUS knock down subsidies ,","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"most Republicans agree","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"they ' ll need to either extend them legislatively","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"or replace the federal help with a health care tax credit .","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"Both options cost money ,","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"which would again scramble the reconciliation puzzle .","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"There ' s even disagreement","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"about whether such a \" fix \" should be part of reconciliation at all .","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"Budget Chairman Tom Price","depth":14},{"id":145,"text":"( R-Ga. )","depth":14},{"id":146,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"enacting a GOP alternative through reconciliation may be even tougher","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"than trying to repeal Obamacare .","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"\" I think","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"it ' s important to do the repeal of Obamacare as much","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"as can be done","depth":16},{"id":152,"text":"given the Senate rules ,","depth":16},{"id":153,"text":"but I don ' t know how you address a [ new policy ] in the health care system , \"","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"The party may have a wild card or two up its sleeve , however .","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"The GOP budget deal allows for the House to score a reconciliation bill \" dynamically , \"","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"meaning Republicans can account for assumed economic growth","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"that will help plug the costs of repeal .","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"Republican staff are also considering","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"whether they can find savings elsewhere","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"to pay for repeal ,","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"just as Democrats made education cuts","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"to help pay for the overhaul in the first place .","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"But even these tricks may not amount to a full repeal ,","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"Hoagland said :","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"\" You can shoot a big hole in [ Obamacare ] .","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"You can put it on the operating table ,","depth":15},{"id":168,"text":"but you can ' t just repeal the whole thing . \"","depth":15}],"relations":[{"parent":337,"left":208,"right":336,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":192,"right":207,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":192,"left":179,"right":191,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":171,"right":178,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":170,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":170,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":173,"right":177,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":172,"right":5,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":6,"right":176,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":7,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":8,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":191,"left":185,"right":190,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":183,"right":184,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":183,"left":182,"right":15,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"paren